# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: MagePath | Scene: MagePath5
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Months passed and seasons turned."
    new "Months passed and seasons turned."

    old "Sarah had lost all relation to time, perhaps even the world outside of the wizard's house."
    new "Sarah had lost all relation to time, perhaps even the world outside of the wizard's house."

    old "There was only the study, and her endless lessons."
    new "There was only the study, and her endless lessons."

    old "Ever since she had seen her home country again, she had become posessed with a purpose."
    new "Ever since she had seen her home country again, she had become posessed with a purpose."

    old "Many nights even Xan would retire to bed earlier than her."
    new "Many nights even Xan would retire to bed earlier than her."

    old "Before, she had engaged with her lessons as if they had simply been classes, the kind she had been taught growing up in Castle Reinmeer."
    new "Before, she had engaged with her lessons as if they had simply been classes, the kind she had been taught growing up in Castle Reinmeer."

    old "Now, she understood them for what they were. The path towards power, towards mastery of magic."
    new "Now, she understood them for what they were. The path towards power, towards mastery of magic."

    old "The thing that would allow her to change the world."
    new "The thing that would allow her to change the world."

    old "Sarah raised up her hand. Guiding the tempo of her movement now came natural to her, no longer forced."
    new "Sarah raised up her hand. Guiding the tempo of her movement now came natural to her, no longer forced."

    old "A muscle long unused but now trained was flexed."
    new "A muscle long unused but now trained was flexed."

    old "The feeling of the energy around her, within her, she had learned to guide it without becoming distracted by it."
    new "The feeling of the energy around her, within her, she had learned to guide it without becoming distracted by it."

    old "Then, all things faded."
    new "Then, all things faded."

    old "There was no more room. No air around her. No noise."
    new "There was no more room. No air around her. No noise."

    old "Only the perfection of her form, the gathering static of her power, and then the utterance of her words."
    new "Only the perfection of her form, the gathering static of her power, and then the utterance of her words."

    old "The passed from her lips as if nearly silent, but in her mind, their meaning screamed and roared as she imprinted her will onto the magical energies."
    new "The passed from her lips as if nearly silent, but in her mind, their meaning screamed and roared as she imprinted her will onto the magical energies."

    old "By her will alone, she crushed, broke, reshaped and forged the magical energies into the shape that she needed...demanded."
    new "By her will alone, she crushed, broke, reshaped and forged the magical energies into the shape that she needed...demanded."

    old "As wind to a hurricane. As water to a tsunami. As a spark to a blaze."
    new "As wind to a hurricane. As water to a tsunami. As a spark to a blaze."

    old "The seperate energies forged together became more than their parts. Sarah extended her palm, and manifested her will."
    new "The seperate energies forged together became more than their parts. Sarah extended her palm, and manifested her will."

    old "From her extended palm, an orb of near pure light erupted, firing off towards Xan."
    new "From her extended palm, an orb of near pure light erupted, firing off towards Xan."

    old "Splitting across the room, the orb crashed into Xan's barrier. Had he not been ready for it, even the mighty mage would have paid dearly."
    new "Splitting across the room, the orb crashed into Xan's barrier. Had he not been ready for it, even the mighty mage would have paid dearly."

    old "Sparks scattered across the room as the orb sliced and spun, its force splintering fragments of Xan's magical shield."
    new "Sparks scattered across the room as the orb sliced and spun, its force splintering fragments of Xan's magical shield."

    old "Sarah looked on, and continued to impress her will upon her creation, pushing the orb deeper into Xan's defenses."
    new "Sarah looked on, and continued to impress her will upon her creation, pushing the orb deeper into Xan's defenses."

    old "Suddenly, she watched as Xan began to move his hand, performing movements and speaking words she had never seen before."
    new "Suddenly, she watched as Xan began to move his hand, performing movements and speaking words she had never seen before."

    old "No sooner did she notice, did the orb's energy dissipate, sparing what was left of the mage's shield."
    new "No sooner did she notice, did the orb's energy dissipate, sparing what was left of the mage's shield."

    old "Not fair. You're using new spells."
    new "Not fair. You're using new spells."

    old "Sorry, but I wasn't about to let my head get taken off for a practice lesson."
    new "Sorry, but I wasn't about to let my head get taken off for a practice lesson."

    old "You mean I was close."
    new "You mean I was close."

    old "My barrier would not have held much longer."
    new "My barrier would not have held much longer."

    old "Sarah eyed Xan. She might have nearly shattered his barrier, but he did not appear to be in much distress about it."
    new "Sarah eyed Xan. She might have nearly shattered his barrier, but he did not appear to be in much distress about it."

    old "So I almost defeated you?"
    new "So I almost defeated you?"

    old "Maybe, if I had kept up the barrier and done nothing else."
    new "Maybe, if I had kept up the barrier and done nothing else."

    old "But you'll have to understand that in a fight, a real fight, no magic user would just stand and absorb your hits like that."
    new "But you'll have to understand that in a fight, a real fight, no magic user would just stand and absorb your hits like that."

    old "In a real fight."
    new "In a real fight."

    old "The mage was gone."
    new "The mage was gone."

    old "Sarah felt his hand slapping the back of her head."
    new "Sarah felt his hand slapping the back of her head."

    old "A real mage would have been moving."
    new "A real mage would have been moving."

    old "There was nobody behind her."
    new "There was nobody behind her."

    old "And you're far from ready for that."
    new "And you're far from ready for that."

    old "Sarah turned back around to face Xan."
    new "Sarah turned back around to face Xan."

    old "Magic. That much should be obvious by now."
    new "Magic. That much should be obvious by now."

    old "That's always your answer to everything."
    new "That's always your answer to everything."

    old "And it's almost always true."
    new "And it's almost always true."

    old "Still...how long before I can do that?"
    new "Still...how long before I can do that?"

    old "Xan considered his answer for a moment."
    new "Xan considered his answer for a moment."

    old "For most, I would say years, but for you Sarah, I don't know. Maybe months, maybe only weeks..."
    new "For most, I would say years, but for you Sarah, I don't know. Maybe months, maybe only weeks..."

    old "You're progressing so much faster than even I could have even dared to hope."
    new "You're progressing so much faster than even I could have even dared to hope."

    old "Sarah smiled at his compliment."
    new "Sarah smiled at his compliment."

    old "She knew she was progressing fast. Even when the mage had said nothing of it, she could see in his face, his stunned surprise by how fast she now mastered certain arts."
    new "She knew she was progressing fast. Even when the mage had said nothing of it, she could see in his face, his stunned surprise by how fast she now mastered certain arts."

    old "A prodigy, huh?."
    new "A prodigy, huh?."

    old "A natural aptitude, but such is no replacement for commitment. That's what's changed."
    new "A natural aptitude, but such is no replacement for commitment. That's what's changed."

    old "You think I wasn't trying before?"
    new "You think I wasn't trying before?"

    old "Maybe you were, but not like you've been working for the last few months."
    new "Maybe you were, but not like you've been working for the last few months."

    old "Sarah knew he was right."
    new "Sarah knew he was right."

    old "Having seen what became of her country, her people..."
    new "Having seen what became of her country, her people..."

    old "But worse than the carnage was knowing she could do nothing for her people. That she had to stand by and let it all happen."
    new "But worse than the carnage was knowing she could do nothing for her people. That she had to stand by and let it all happen."

    old "She would never let herself be that weak again."
    new "She would never let herself be that weak again."

    old "I think it just took some time to click for me, you know?"
    new "I think it just took some time to click for me, you know?"

    old "Sarah could see Xan studying her. Trying to unravel her inner thoughts."
    new "Sarah could see Xan studying her. Trying to unravel her inner thoughts."

    old "Could he see, she wondered, what was in her mind?"
    new "Could he see, she wondered, what was in her mind?"

    old "Magic comes to each in their own speed. For you perhaps faster than most, but still, you should not push yourself too much. There is plenty of time."
    new "Magic comes to each in their own speed. For you perhaps faster than most, but still, you should not push yourself too much. There is plenty of time."

    old "Plenty of time?"
    new "Plenty of time?"

    old "Xan paused for a moment."
    new "Xan paused for a moment."

    old "Of course. You have a lifetime to master it."
    new "Of course. You have a lifetime to master it."

    old "Sarah wasn't a fool. She knew that wasn't what he had meant to say. Still, it was pointless to press him."
    new "Sarah wasn't a fool. She knew that wasn't what he had meant to say. Still, it was pointless to press him."

    old "Xan had habit of going his own pace. Only revealing what he wanted to, and never a fraction more. She decided to drop it."
    new "Xan had habit of going his own pace. Only revealing what he wanted to, and never a fraction more. She decided to drop it."

    old "So, now that I've mastered that spell, what comes next?"
    new "So, now that I've mastered that spell, what comes next?"

    old "I hardly doubt you've mastered it."
    new "I hardly doubt you've mastered it."

    old "Fine, whatever, I can do it just fine. I want to know what comes next."
    new "Fine, whatever, I can do it just fine. I want to know what comes next."

    old "Didn't I just say you shouldn't rush?"
    new "Didn't I just say you shouldn't rush?"

    old "I've barely broken a sweat. I can keep going."
    new "I've barely broken a sweat. I can keep going."

    old "You, maybe, but I'm not as young as I may appear. Holding off those attacks takes a lot out of me."
    new "You, maybe, but I'm not as young as I may appear. Holding off those attacks takes a lot out of me."

    old "She watched Xan shuffle across the room, dropping down into his chair."
    new "She watched Xan shuffle across the room, dropping down into his chair."

    old "There were other things she could do. Train by herself. Study even more. But something kept her here."
    new "There were other things she could do. Train by herself. Study even more. But something kept her here."

    old "Had it been what he said earlier?"
    new "Had it been what he said earlier?"

    old "What comes after this?"
    new "What comes after this?"

    old "The next spell? Ooh, I'll have to see, I'm thinking your first transubstantion spell, that should prove a challenge."
    new "The next spell? Ooh, I'll have to see, I'm thinking your first transubstantion spell, that should prove a challenge."

    old "No, I'm not talking about the next spell, or the spell after that."
    new "No, I'm not talking about the next spell, or the spell after that."

    old "I'm asking where this road leads to? In the long term."
    new "I'm asking where this road leads to? In the long term."

    old "You'll be my apprentice for a few years more, until I decide you've learned enough."
    new "You'll be my apprentice for a few years more, until I decide you've learned enough."

    old "Then you'll be introduced to the masters in the citadel, who can decide whether you're ready."
    new "Then you'll be introduced to the masters in the citadel, who can decide whether you're ready."

    old "If they allow it, you will be included into our order as a mage of the first tower."
    new "If they allow it, you will be included into our order as a mage of the first tower."

    old "From there, you will continue your studies. Every few years you will advance, if you learn enough, to the ranks tower."
    new "From there, you will continue your studies. Every few years you will advance, if you learn enough, to the ranks tower."

    old "When you're a mage of the fifth tower, you will be allowed to take on an apprentice."
    new "When you're a mage of the fifth tower, you will be allowed to take on an apprentice."

    old "Then you will teach them as I taught you."
    new "Then you will teach them as I taught you."

    old "Maybe one day, centuries from now, you can retire to the elder circle, guide our order, and so on."
    new "Maybe one day, centuries from now, you can retire to the elder circle, guide our order, and so on."

    old "Sarah listened as Xan painted a picture of her life."
    new "Sarah listened as Xan painted a picture of her life."

    old "Exactly. This life of ours, studying magic, it can be very orderly. Very measured."
    new "Exactly. This life of ours, studying magic, it can be very orderly. Very measured."

    old "You'll always know where you stand."
    new "You'll always know where you stand."

    old "It did sound nice to Sarah. Clean, orderly, decisive. No more doubt."
    new "It did sound nice to Sarah. Clean, orderly, decisive. No more doubt."

    old "That sounds horrible."
    new "That sounds horrible."

    old "To be locked away in some citadel? Studying for centuries, all to what end? So I can watch the world turn by?"
    new "To be locked away in some citadel? Studying for centuries, all to what end? So I can watch the world turn by?"

    old "The opposite. From that vantage point, you will see the world."
    new "The opposite. From that vantage point, you will see the world."

    old "Rather than be trapped inside of it, you can watch the turning of human society."
    new "Rather than be trapped inside of it, you can watch the turning of human society."

    old "Yeah, by standing outside of it, detached."
    new "Yeah, by standing outside of it, detached."

    old "It's horrid. That's no way to live."
    new "It's horrid. That's no way to live."

    old "Xan waved his hand as if to dismiss her."
    new "Xan waved his hand as if to dismiss her."

    old "You'll learn to appreciate it."
    new "You'll learn to appreciate it."

    old "Sarah doubted that she ever would."
    new "Sarah doubted that she ever would."

    old "But what about you?"
    new "But what about you?"

    old "Xan looked up surprised."
    new "Xan looked up surprised."

    old "You're in here, out in the real world. You're not in the citadel, you're not studying in any tower."
    new "You're in here, out in the real world. You're not in the citadel, you're not studying in any tower."

    old "That's true, but I have my own labors to attend to."
    new "That's true, but I have my own labors to attend to."

    old "Studying all alone in this house?"
    new "Studying all alone in this house?"

    old "I get out, don't worry. Endless doors and rooms lead to ever corner of the world."
    new "I get out, don't worry. Endless doors and rooms lead to ever corner of the world."

    old "Before I ran into you, I was quite busy."
    new "Before I ran into you, I was quite busy."

    old "Sarah looked at Xan, trying to gain a measure of him."
    new "Sarah looked at Xan, trying to gain a measure of him."

    old "Doing what?"
    new "Doing what?"

    old "My works."
    new "My works."

    old "Which are."
    new "Which are."

    old "None of your concern, apprentice."
    new "None of your concern, apprentice."

    old "Xan kept a smile on his face as he spoke."
    new "Xan kept a smile on his face as he spoke."

    old "You do this a lot, you know. Keeping me in the dark..."
    new "You do this a lot, you know. Keeping me in the dark..."

    old "I've taught you magic, isn't that enough?"
    new "I've taught you magic, isn't that enough?"

    old "For all you've taught me, for all you've done for me, I still barely know you any better than when we first met."
    new "For all you've taught me, for all you've done for me, I still barely know you any better than when we first met."

    old "Do teachers and students need to be friends?"
    new "Do teachers and students need to be friends?"

    old "I'm not asking to be your friend. I just wish you'd let me understand what it is you do. It can't just be magic for magic's sake, I don't believe it."
    new "I'm not asking to be your friend. I just wish you'd let me understand what it is you do. It can't just be magic for magic's sake, I don't believe it."

    old "Xan rapped his knuckles across the desk."
    new "Xan rapped his knuckles across the desk."

    old "We spoke of it, months ago when I took you to visit Rosanna."
    new "We spoke of it, months ago when I took you to visit Rosanna."

    old "Memories flooded Sarah's mind. Memories she hoped would stay buried."
    new "Memories flooded Sarah's mind. Memories she hoped would stay buried."

    old "As mages, we live very long lives. And as an order, we observe the world from far above."
    new "As mages, we live very long lives. And as an order, we observe the world from far above."

    old "But, while we observe, we do not only observe."
    new "But, while we observe, we do not only observe."

    old "The council has plans, designs, that it hopes can come about."
    new "The council has plans, designs, that it hopes can come about."

    old "The council believes that with the proper guidance, we can steer this world towards peace, towards a future where the horrors of war, famine and all other tragedies can be done away with."
    new "The council believes that with the proper guidance, we can steer this world towards peace, towards a future where the horrors of war, famine and all other tragedies can be done away with."

    old "A future where every soul, be it a king or a peasant, will be valued and safeguarded."
    new "A future where every soul, be it a king or a peasant, will be valued and safeguarded."

    old "Sarah listened intently as Xan spoke."
    new "Sarah listened intently as Xan spoke."

    old "It sounds like a fantasy."
    new "It sounds like a fantasy."

    old "Perhaps, and it certainly is for now. But you do not see as we have seen."
    new "Perhaps, and it certainly is for now. But you do not see as we have seen."

    old "The world is brutal, but it used to be much more so."
    new "The world is brutal, but it used to be much more so."

    old "That is what we offer. A steady hand. And that is what I do, and some others. We are agents of that steady hand, seeking to implement this project of peace."
    new "That is what we offer. A steady hand. And that is what I do, and some others. We are agents of that steady hand, seeking to implement this project of peace."

    old "You pretend to be everywhere, and yet, I barely saw a single mage in my entire life."
    new "You pretend to be everywhere, and yet, I barely saw a single mage in my entire life."

    old "And that's how the council likes it."
    new "And that's how the council likes it."

    old "We are powerful, but we are few. We cannot bend this world through brute force, even if we might have a lot of it."
    new "We are powerful, but we are few. We cannot bend this world through brute force, even if we might have a lot of it."

    old "This world needs a steady hand, but that hand must also be gentle."
    new "This world needs a steady hand, but that hand must also be gentle."

    old "A nudge here, a tug there."
    new "A nudge here, a tug there."

    old "Slowly we help the world along, to bring about the paradise that must be."
    new "Slowly we help the world along, to bring about the paradise that must be."

    old "And Rosanna? That's just a stepping stone towards that paradise?"
    new "And Rosanna? That's just a stepping stone towards that paradise?"

    old "It will sound cruel, but I will be honest with you Sarah, yes."
    new "It will sound cruel, but I will be honest with you Sarah, yes."

    old "Your nation held millions of people, but it is home to less than one-hundreth of the world's total population."
    new "Your nation held millions of people, but it is home to less than one-hundreth of the world's total population."

    old "I know the names of nations long forgotten. I walked their streets and witnessed them fall into ruin. Do you weep for them?"
    new "I know the names of nations long forgotten. I walked their streets and witnessed them fall into ruin. Do you weep for them?"

    old "You don't, because they mean nothing to you, and Rosanna still means everything to you."
    new "You don't, because they mean nothing to you, and Rosanna still means everything to you."

    old "But that is a flaw in your perspective, a flaw that you will learn to overcome in the years that follow."
    new "But that is a flaw in your perspective, a flaw that you will learn to overcome in the years that follow."

    old "Sarah listened to what Xan told her."
    new "Sarah listened to what Xan told her."

    old "Sarah watched the mage retire to his room and sat by herself as night set in."
    new "Sarah watched the mage retire to his room and sat by herself as night set in."

    old "Maybe he was right. But the thought alone scared her."
    new "Maybe he was right. But the thought alone scared her."

    old "Could she ever become like him? Stand idly by and watch innocents suffer, because some great design demands it?"
    new "Could she ever become like him? Stand idly by and watch innocents suffer, because some great design demands it?"

    old "Would she even want to be that cold?"
    new "Would she even want to be that cold?"

    old "She wanted power, enough to reshape the world, but what if following this path would change her?"
    new "She wanted power, enough to reshape the world, but what if following this path would change her?"

    old "What if she gained the power to change the world, but in the process lost the will to change it?"
    new "What if she gained the power to change the world, but in the process lost the will to change it?"

    old "She had put herself upon this path to forget the painful memories of her home, but she now found her mind drifting to Rosanna more than ever."
    new "She had put herself upon this path to forget the painful memories of her home, but she now found her mind drifting to Rosanna more than ever."

